		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=223272"><span id=>fhrugby</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>128 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.55]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I recommend the following (not the exact words use /do # for the appropriate skill)<br>a) &quot;evade + macro&quot;<br>/attack off<br>/hide (evade)<br>/pickpockets or /beg when pp maxed for that level<br>/attack on<br><br>b) &quot;backstab + macro&quot;<br>/backstab<br>/sense traps<br>/disarm trap<br>/loc<br><br>By including beg, pickpocket, sense and disarm traps in these macros you will get those skills up while doing the every day combat actions you do normally and not require extra actions. You will need the pickpocket for the Epic, sense and disarm traps for LDON and there is an uber charm based on a couple of skills which include begging so might as well get that up as well.<br><br>Just a side note , while actually in a LDON dungeon you will encounter actual traps and you might want to disable the sense traps portion as you will spin towards the trap in battle which may make you not see your target. I would leave disarm traps, but do not use right next to a container. I usually leave a backstab button on hotkeys for direct backstab so I can see when timer is up. I use that button when near containers or near traps that make me spin and I do not change the macro.<br> <br>I include /loc in bs macro because it enable an easy to hit loc hotkey for those moments I am about to die and will need to know where corpse is, w/o using up a hotkey spot.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Baron McSean Shadowraider level 59 Halfling Rogue,<br>Cullum Level 36 Dwarf Paladin<br>Leapof Faith 24 Froglok Cleric<br>Necrosaurous Level 23 Iksar Necromancer<br>Xauvian Level 1 Trader Mule Extraordinaire<br>XEGONY SERVER</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=9767692599789&num=7&page=0&post=1&mid=9767692599789><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">7 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class2">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
